contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

02:40.500 --> 02:43.411
I'll tell ya, glad you're here.
I didn't think you'd make it.

02:43.491 --> 02:45.356
Heard they're closing the highway tonight.

02:45.436 --> 02:48.682
Not yet. Fire's still 65 miles out.

02:48.762 --> 02:49.817
Yeah?

02:49.897 --> 02:52.152
Thanks. Cheers.

02:52.232 --> 02:54.500
You're sweating like a pig, Barrett.

02:57.270 --> 02:59.747
- What's the buy-in?
- Hundred bucks.

02:59.827 --> 03:01.629
What's the game?

03:01.709 --> 03:03.597
- Texas hold 'em.
- Guy's robbing me blind.

03:03.677 --> 03:07.568
So, what, it's just the three of us?
Where's Carl and everybody?

03:07.648 --> 03:11.205
Well, he's up at Fort Yukon.
He won't be back for a couple weeks and...

03:11.285 --> 03:13.607
Wade's got his boy tonight.
What the hell is his name...

03:13.687 --> 03:15.955
- Matthew.
- Matthew, yeah.

03:19.252 --> 03:22.262
- Hey, are you in or what?
- Duty calls.

03:31.104 --> 03:32.479
Hello?

03:32.559 --> 03:36.185
- Did I wake you?
- <i>No, I'm up.</i>

03:38.044 --> 03:40.067
How was your meeting?

03:40.147 --> 03:42.670
<i>Well, all that's left are the signatures.</i>

03:42.750 --> 03:45.418
- Good.
- Drive was a stretch.

03:46.352 --> 03:49.543
- <i>Where are you now?</i>
- Lou's.

03:49.623 --> 03:51.157
<i>Okay.</i>

03:51.858 --> 03:53.681
<i>I think I might go to bed.</i>

03:54.361 --> 03:55.817
'Night.

03:56.197 --> 03:57.764
'Night.

04:00.833 --> 04:04.892
All I'm saying is you have
to have options. That's all.

04:04.972 --> 04:07.194
Without options,
you're gonna end up finding...

04:07.274 --> 04:10.097
You young kids,
you're only out chasing a buck.

04:10.177 --> 04:13.033
You don't know the meaning
of the word principle.

04:13.113 --> 04:15.603
- A man's gotta have principles. Am I right?
- That's right.

04:15.683 --> 04:18.505
But think about how much money
you'd make selling this?

04:18.584 --> 04:21.317
OExcuse me if I'm mistaken, but...

04:21.398 --> 04:23.798
...people still need to eat and drink, yeah?

04:24.158 --> 04:27.114
Alright, but think about the competition?

04:27.194 --> 04:29.795
- You got... you got...
- Are we gonna finish this hand?

04:30.536 --> 04:35.222
Yeah, big corporations and chains,
franchises breathing down your neck.

04:35.322 --> 04:38.379
- Yeah.
- We've got to move with the times.

04:38.459 --> 04:41.582
Now, when we have a republican
in the White House...

04:41.662 --> 04:45.464
- ...come November, I'll tell you this...
- What the fuck are you talking about?

04:46.533 --> 04:49.290
We can only hope. And I'll drink to that.

04:49.370 --> 04:51.768
- Cheers.
- How do you live with yourself?

04:53.474 --> 04:56.331
This hand will never change, will it?

04:58.511 --> 05:00.562
Excuse me, we're closed.

05:03.249 --> 05:05.973
- Fucking kids. No respect for anyone.
- I got it.

05:06.053 --> 05:09.656
- No, no, no. Don't do anything, just...
- Lou, stop.

05:15.261 --> 05:18.396
- Maybe you didn't hear our friend...
- Can I have...

05:18.476 --> 05:20.304
...the early bird special?

05:20.834 --> 05:22.390
What?

05:22.770 --> 05:24.659
The early bird special?

05:25.039 --> 05:27.073
With a glass of water, please.

05:28.541 --> 05:31.765
You need to go right now.

05:32.245 --> 05:33.767
No.

05:33.847 --> 05:35.702
I can't.

05:37.447 --> 05:39.284
I'm hungry.

05:41.721 --> 05:44.745
Maybe you're not understanding
what I'm saying.

05:44.825 --> 05:48.021
Do you... do you have a wife...

05:48.101 --> 05:50.959
...that you have to get home to, Mitchel?

05:51.598 --> 05:53.465
Is it Mitchel?

05:54.300 --> 05:56.090
Is your name Mitchel?

05:56.170 --> 05:59.545
- Do I know you?
- I don't know.

06:00.106 --> 06:02.830
Just be straight with me.

06:02.910 --> 06:04.711
I'm being straight with you.

06:06.909 --> 06:08.945
Can I have the early bird special?

06:10.516 --> 06:12.018
Please?

06:12.852 --> 06:14.909
Get the fuck out right now.

06:15.289 --> 06:17.070
Get the fuck out right now.

06:22.161 --> 06:24.029
One, two.

06:45.151 --> 06:46.974
So what's going on?

06:47.354 --> 06:49.177
What the hell was that about?

06:50.257 --> 06:52.340
Why'd you speak to him like that?

06:55.177 --> 06:58.181
I'd have done a lot more given the chance.

06:59.465 --> 07:01.267
Well, who the hell was he?

07:05.805 --> 07:08.463
I don't know. I don't think he was from here.

07:09.093 --> 07:10.976
He was...

07:12.879 --> 07:14.710
Maybe we should call it a night.

07:18.117 --> 07:19.652
Hey!

07:20.553 --> 07:22.388
I told you we're closed.

11:26.198 --> 11:28.855
- Morning, sunshine.
- Hey, Sam. Is this too loud?

11:28.935 --> 11:30.824
Not even a little bit.

11:31.204 --> 11:34.127
- Coffee fresh?
- Made it this morning.

11:34.207 --> 11:37.498
You're an angel, Mags. Heaven sent.

11:37.978 --> 11:40.500
- Tell you that too much?
- Nope.

11:40.580 --> 11:43.036
That's a good thing. Want to know why?

11:43.116 --> 11:46.223
- Why?
- 'Cause I ain't never gonna quit.

11:46.603 --> 11:48.375
- Good morning.
- Good morning.

11:48.455 --> 11:51.657
- Where's Rosie?
- She's on cleaning duty.

11:52.791 --> 11:56.462
- No school today?
- Yeah, not till 9:30.

11:59.431 --> 12:01.901
I got another complaint about room 128.

12:05.197 --> 12:10.297
Hey, Sam, I was wondering, could I pick up
a few extra shifts before the holidays?

12:10.377 --> 12:14.334
- Thinking about going on a trip.
- Trip? Where you thinking about going?

12:14.414 --> 12:17.170
Don't know yet. Any ideas?

12:17.250 --> 12:21.508
If I were you,
I'd just head out to Spruce Valley.

12:21.988 --> 12:24.377
I was thinking something more like Florida.

12:24.457 --> 12:25.679
- God.
- What?

12:25.759 --> 12:27.915
- You don't go to Florida on purpose, Mags.
- Why?

12:27.995 --> 12:32.119
I'll tell you one thing, I'll tell you that,
'cause Florida... Florida, it's not a trip.

12:32.199 --> 12:34.804
- It's a death sentence.
- What are you jaded?

12:34.884 --> 12:36.935
Jaded. Spell jaded.

12:38.805 --> 12:42.696
There's no end to my wisdom, Mags.
One of these days you are gonna realize that.

12:42.776 --> 12:44.598
You coming to the game?

12:44.678 --> 12:48.168
What kind of question is that?
Am I coming? What do I always tell you?

12:48.248 --> 12:51.972
"I'm the best goddamn point guard
the Mustangs ever had."

12:52.052 --> 12:54.608
It's not just the best,
it's the most generous.

12:54.688 --> 12:57.626
- Never underestimate the power of generosity.
- What are you looking for?

12:57.706 --> 12:59.479
- Papers. Where are the papers?
- Right here.

12:59.559 --> 13:02.749
Thank you. Of course
I'm gonna come to the game.

13:02.829 --> 13:06.097
- I wouldn't miss it for the world.
- Good, 'cause I need a ride.

13:07.167 --> 13:09.401
Well played. You got me.

13:13.672 --> 13:16.496
Are you going to Bernadette's for the wake?

13:16.576 --> 13:18.131
Well...

13:18.211 --> 13:20.045
...I think we all should.

13:20.980 --> 13:22.836
It's real nice of her.

13:23.116 --> 13:25.537
Considering there was no public burial.

13:28.220 --> 13:29.783
There's no...

13:29.863 --> 13:33.697
...there's no words for what these
people are going through, Mags.

13:33.777 --> 13:35.660
No word.

13:48.340 --> 13:51.364
- Disgusting, every single time.
- Well, go to the store.

13:51.444 --> 13:55.335
I'm sure it's just two miles
down the road. It's walking distance.

13:55.415 --> 13:57.638
Mr. Barnes, it's the manager.

13:58.218 --> 14:00.019
Fucking hell.

14:04.590 --> 14:06.713
How you doing, Mr. Barnes? It's Sam.

14:06.793 --> 14:10.584
You know, I'm the manager here at the motel.
I think we met a few days back, right?

14:10.664 --> 14:12.152
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

14:12.232 --> 14:14.855
Look, I hate to bother you, I really do. I...

14:14.935 --> 14:17.457
- I like to... I like to let people sorta...
- What do you want?

14:17.537 --> 14:22.182
Well, unfortunately there's been a couple
of complaints here about your room, see...

14:22.262 --> 14:25.303
- ...and... I'm just...
- Wait a second. What kind of complaints?

14:25.383 --> 14:29.072
Well, noise, sir. There's quite a bit
of noise I here coming out of here...

14:29.152 --> 14:33.010
...and if you could just do me a favor
just try to keep the noise down.

14:39.625 --> 14:41.505
Sure told him?

14:42.095 --> 14:43.896
I laid it down, didn't I?

14:45.130 --> 14:47.154
Good day at the office, sweetheart.

14:47.484 --> 14:49.351
Do good.

15:32.344 --> 15:34.146
You alright?

15:35.913 --> 15:37.437
Yeah.

15:37.817 --> 15:39.840
We were wondering where you were.

15:40.420 --> 15:42.409
There's a big turnout down there.

15:42.489 --> 15:45.524
Josephine thinks somebody
should make a speech.

15:48.994 --> 15:51.229
I wanted to thank you for...

15:52.164 --> 15:54.188
...putting all of this together.

15:55.035 --> 15:58.024
That's all. I gotta run,
it's my mom's waiting.

15:58.104 --> 16:00.572
What am I supposed to do with all his stuff?

16:02.474 --> 16:04.932
We just threw Mitchel's stuff out.

16:05.712 --> 16:09.715
'Cause Mom says it's part
of the cleansing process. A fresh start.

16:11.250 --> 16:14.253
He was a man, Lila.

16:15.187 --> 16:16.985
I know.

16:18.057 --> 16:20.525
I know what you're saying. I do.

16:21.393 --> 16:24.217
- You're not alone.
- I'm sorry.

16:24.297 --> 16:26.502
I mean, listen to me complain.

16:28.233 --> 16:31.558
You and Mitchel didn't get
three years of marriage.

16:31.638 --> 16:34.039
That doesn't mean I've got it any worse.

16:39.328 --> 16:41.363
Maybe they're some place better.

16:43.382 --> 16:45.216
In peace.

16:46.018 --> 16:47.553
Maybe.

16:49.254 --> 16:51.857
Still haven't shed a goddamn tear.

16:53.058 --> 16:55.348
Eighteen years of marriage...

16:55.428 --> 16:57.293
...not one.

16:58.664 --> 17:00.520
It's disgraceful.

17:00.700 --> 17:02.735
You shouldn't talk that way.

17:05.671 --> 17:07.873
I wasn't the best wife, Lila.

17:11.109 --> 17:13.145
I could've been better.

17:15.446 --> 17:17.337
You look organized.

17:17.416 --> 17:19.218
It's all Tom.

17:20.685 --> 17:23.271
Well, Tom didn't really
trust the banks. Did he?

17:23.352 --> 17:24.477
Nope.

17:24.557 --> 17:27.180
Mitchel just always thought
he was avoiding taxes.

17:27.260 --> 17:29.749
Yeah, everyone did...

17:29.829 --> 17:31.703
...but he was right.

17:32.032 --> 17:35.294
Why pay someone an arm
and a leg to keep what's yours?

17:40.773 --> 17:43.196
You let me know if you need anything, okay?

17:44.176 --> 17:47.216
- I'm so sorry, Bernie.
- Yeah.

17:47.896 --> 17:49.880
Me too.

17:50.549 --> 17:52.351
Fucking mess.

17:54.420 --> 17:57.689
Cheryl's having nightmares. Girls too.

18:00.125 --> 18:01.927
What's the chief say?

18:03.962 --> 18:07.841
Well, it's his jurisdiction, but...

18:07.921 --> 18:11.202
...he's talking about bringing
some boys from upstate.

18:12.137 --> 18:16.129
Last thing we need, city officials...

18:16.209 --> 18:18.877
...flashing their badges, asking questions.

18:20.576 --> 18:22.135
Well...

18:22.315 --> 18:24.371
...people want answers, Marty.

18:25.151 --> 18:28.041
- Am I interrupting?
- No, not at all.

18:28.121 --> 18:29.954
Just on my way.

18:30.622 --> 18:33.258
Once again, Bernie, my condolences.

18:34.927 --> 18:36.983
- Cheryl gives her love.
- Thanks.

18:37.063 --> 18:39.064
- Sam.
- Yeah.

18:54.196 --> 18:56.014
Christ, Bern, I...

18:58.684 --> 19:00.508
...don't know what to say.

19:01.788 --> 19:03.789
You don't have to say anything.

19:05.190 --> 19:06.725
Yeah.

19:12.798 --> 19:14.622
Your hair's getting long.

19:16.102 --> 19:17.958
I need to cut it again.

19:18.638 --> 19:20.193
Yeah.

19:20.773 --> 19:22.841
You think I could come by tonight?

19:24.543 --> 19:26.366
I don't know, Bern.

19:26.946 --> 19:28.947
You think that's a good idea?

20:26.438 --> 20:27.939
Elwood?

20:30.375 --> 20:32.372
Ever been to California?

20:32.452 --> 20:35.113
- What?
- California.

20:36.048 --> 20:38.871
My mom was from there.
El Cerrito or some shit.

20:38.951 --> 20:41.908
Born in 1949. You ever been there?

20:41.988 --> 20:43.989
- No.
- No.

20:45.390 --> 20:47.192
Think I wanna go there.

20:52.431 --> 20:54.486
Why did you kill those men?

20:55.434 --> 20:57.323
I did my job.

20:57.603 --> 21:00.593
It was supposed to be just Mitchel.
That's all.

21:00.673 --> 21:04.270
I sent Miles a picture. The one from
last Christmas 'with the beige sweater...

21:04.350 --> 21:07.066
- ...'cause I remember...
- No, no, no, no, no, no, no, no.

21:07.146 --> 21:09.436
This isn't Miles' deal anymore.

21:10.016 --> 21:13.473
- I did what had to be done.
- I didn't ask for this.

21:13.953 --> 21:16.976
- Those other men didn't deserve...
- Your husband wasn't coming out of the bar.

21:17.056 --> 21:21.247
It is as simple as that. I was told
he was gonna be out by midnight.

21:21.327 --> 21:23.181
So whose fault is it?

21:25.197 --> 21:28.187
They think it was a robbery.
Fuck! You should be celebrating.

21:28.267 --> 21:30.668
Tell me when I'm gonna get my money.

21:31.503 --> 21:34.827
You don't have to worry about it.
It's all taken care of.

21:34.907 --> 21:37.130
Okay. When?

21:37.710 --> 21:39.432
- Didn't Miles expl...
- When?

21:39.512 --> 21:44.446
This week! I'm gonna go see
our la... Mitchel's lawyer.

21:45.350 --> 21:48.007
I'm owed 50. You remember that.

21:48.087 --> 21:50.722
There's plenty. Mitchel was good with money.

21:52.457 --> 21:54.259
Why did you want him dead?

21:55.660 --> 21:57.496
Did he beat you up?

21:58.764 --> 22:00.598
Something like that?

22:01.867 --> 22:03.401
No.

22:04.236 --> 22:05.737
No.

22:07.406 --> 22:09.608
He was always cheating on me.

22:13.745 --> 22:15.981
Mitchel was a fucking pig.

22:17.182 --> 22:18.983
There you go.

22:25.650 --> 22:27.232
I'll give you my number.

22:29.361 --> 22:31.629
Call me if you need.

22:36.101 --> 22:39.225
Maybe if all... this all works out, I...

22:39.305 --> 22:41.194
...I'll take you to dinner.

22:41.274 --> 22:43.497
Movie, something like that.

22:44.177 --> 22:46.099
What? No.

22:47.179 --> 22:49.081
I'm just kidding.

22:51.616 --> 22:54.764
I don't need to tell you
what's gonna happen...

22:54.844 --> 22:57.872
...if I don't get the money that I'm owed.

22:59.891 --> 23:01.443
You understand?

23:04.129 --> 23:06.519
- Yeah.
- Okay.

23:06.599 --> 23:08.132
Okay.

23:51.243 --> 23:53.044
I brought you a book.

23:56.648 --> 23:58.449
No one saw me.

24:18.003 --> 24:20.238
I really wanna cut this hair.

24:21.473 --> 24:23.196
For what?

24:23.276 --> 24:26.345
You just wanna put me
in a beauty contest, don't you?

24:28.196 --> 24:29.998
It's a lost cause, Bern.

24:31.484 --> 24:33.349
No, you're not.

24:39.491 --> 24:41.361
I love you.

24:41.661 --> 24:43.495
You're out of your mind.

24:46.865 --> 24:48.666
You're a good man.

24:56.708 --> 24:58.543
Tom was a good man.

25:00.946 --> 25:02.514
Right?

25:04.282 --> 25:05.850
Yeah.

25:07.786 --> 25:09.855
I don't know, Bern, it's just...

25:11.256 --> 25:13.458
- ...I liked him, you know?
- Yeah.

25:19.865 --> 25:21.933
Where do you think he is?

25:25.270 --> 25:27.110
I don't know, Bernie.

25:29.458 --> 25:30.976
Heaven.

25:33.044 --> 25:34.846
You really believe that?

25:39.918 --> 25:41.419
No.

25:43.421 --> 25:45.257
I think he's still here.

25:47.859 --> 25:50.495
- I can feel him.
- Yeah.

25:54.532 --> 25:56.956
He'll always be with you, Bern.

25:57.036 --> 25:59.704
We hadn't made love in five years.

26:01.873 --> 26:03.741
I don't know.

26:05.310 --> 26:07.946
You get weighed down by convenience...

26:09.047 --> 26:10.915
...I guess.

26:13.185 --> 26:15.620
You can't overlook something like that.

27:11.643 --> 27:13.265
Hi.

27:13.345 --> 27:17.302
- How ya doing?
- Oh, sorry. My name is Elwood.

27:17.382 --> 27:19.105
'Kay. Sam.

27:19.185 --> 27:21.307
- Hi, Sam. Nice to meet ya.
- Yeah.

27:21.387 --> 27:23.543
I'm staying in room 125.

27:23.623 --> 27:26.045
A pretty girl checked me
in a few nights back.

27:26.125 --> 27:29.072
I said that I'd be out
by this evening, but...

27:29.152 --> 27:32.591
- ...there's been a slight change of plan.
- Yeah, no problem, let me just...

27:32.671 --> 27:34.877
...just check the book.

27:34.957 --> 27:36.816
You said...

27:37.136 --> 27:40.059
- You said, what, 1... 125?
- 1...

27:40.139 --> 27:43.996
1-2-5. That's the one. I was hoping I could
just hold on to it for a couple more days.

27:44.076 --> 27:47.633
Okay. Yeah. Yeah, room's all yours. It's...

27:47.713 --> 27:49.502
Oh, great.

27:49.882 --> 27:51.883
Just doing my job, is all.

27:56.521 --> 27:59.157
- You a Nazi?
- Sorry?

28:01.826 --> 28:03.628
Oh, the...

28:04.395 --> 28:06.452
...used to belong to my grandfather.

28:06.532 --> 28:09.916
He took it off a German soldier
there in the war.

28:09.996 --> 28:11.824
He use to tell us that he used it too.

28:11.904 --> 28:14.060
He never would've made it home
without it, he said.

28:14.740 --> 28:17.438
What happened to the man that
it belonged to? The German did...

28:17.518 --> 28:20.032
- ...did your grandfather shoot him?
- He said he didn't.

28:20.112 --> 28:22.635
I guess he just... found the guy there.

28:22.715 --> 28:27.773
He was slumped under a tree and he was
holding on to a picture of sweetheart, so...

28:27.853 --> 28:32.290
- How'd he die then?
- I don't know. Broken heart, I guess.

28:33.124 --> 28:37.584
- Better than a bullet.
- Yeah, maybe, maybe not, right?

28:38.664 --> 28:43.858
- I'm real glad we got this worked out...
- Holy fuck! Holy fucking shit!

28:43.938 --> 28:46.826
- What?
- I knew it.

28:46.906 --> 28:51.897
I knew it as soon as I saw you outside.
That's you! You're the young rodeo champ.

28:51.977 --> 28:54.900
- The bull rider, Russo.
- Well, Rossi.

28:54.980 --> 28:58.350
- Rossi. That's what it is.
- Not so young anymore, but, yes.

28:58.430 --> 29:01.874
Man, my daddy would have a heart attack
if he could see you right now, you know that?

29:01.954 --> 29:04.476
- Is that right?
- He's a Virginia man too, like yourself.

29:04.556 --> 29:06.479
- Okay. Which part?
- He raised me in Lynchburg.

29:06.559 --> 29:09.200
- Okay. Okay. Yeah.
- Yeah. Wow.

29:09.280 --> 29:12.151
He used to drive out to all your shows.
He used to go out of state too.

29:12.231 --> 29:14.119
- Wyoming, Tennessee.
- Okay.

29:14.199 --> 29:17.116
He used to save all your newspaper
clippings with your pictures...

29:17.196 --> 29:18.891
...he worshipped the ground
that you walked on.

29:18.971 --> 29:20.092
Okay.

29:20.172 --> 29:21.961
- Wow.
- Yeah.

29:22.041 --> 29:24.730
Hey, you must get recognized here. Right?

29:24.810 --> 29:27.767
It must get on your nerves all the time.
People coming up to you and everything.

29:27.847 --> 29:30.403
No. I mean, up here people,
they don't know about that.

29:30.483 --> 29:33.339
If they did, they forgot.
Doesn't really bother me either way, so...

29:33.419 --> 29:36.004
- They're fucking idiots.
- Well, you know, it's just...

29:36.084 --> 29:38.344
...it's far away from Virginia is all, so...

